'created_at': '2022-02-01T03:32:40Z', 'updated_at': '2022-02-01T03:32:40Z', 'author_association': 'COLLABORATOR', 'body': "Hi all, 

This is a cool feature but should we be pushing the main version of compose to an alpha from a RC (almost stable)?

I noticed it was for a beta studio feature anyway too? Thoughts?

I know you could argue Compose for Wear OS is in alpha so an alpha for compose itself as well isn't a big deal but I thought it might be better for devs to see we rely on a production version (or close to it) of Compose itself. Might help with the larger partners who want more stability.

Maybe not, but I thought I would asked as I noticed this change as I was finishing up my [PR](https://github.com/android/wear-os-samples/pull/204).
